---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Custom40k Wiki">
  <div class="intro">
    <img src="/custom40k-logo.png" alt="Custom40k" class="intro-logo" width="260" />
    <h1 class="intro-title">Custom40k Wiki</h1>
    <p class="intro-tagline"><span class="typing-line" data-text="Rules · Factions · Armory · Missions"></span></p>

    <div class="ordo-card-outer reveal">
      <img src="/servo-skull.png" class="ordo-skull-img" alt="" />
      <div class="ordo-card">
        <div class="ordo-card-clips">
          <svg width="20" height="26" viewBox="0 0 20 26" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true"><ellipse cx="10" cy="4" rx="5" ry="3.5" fill="none" stroke="#7a6535" stroke-width="2"/><rect x="3" y="6" width="14" height="12" rx="2" fill="#9a8050"/><rect x="1" y="16" width="18" height="6" rx="2" fill="#7a6535"/><circle cx="10" cy="12" r="2.2" fill="#c0a870"/><circle cx="10" cy="12" r="1" fill="#e8d090"/></svg>
          <svg width="20" height="26" viewBox="0 0 20 26" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true"><ellipse cx="10" cy="4" rx="5" ry="3.5" fill="none" stroke="#7a6535" stroke-width="2"/><rect x="3" y="6" width="14" height="12" rx="2" fill="#9a8050"/><rect x="1" y="16" width="18" height="6" rx="2" fill="#7a6535"/><circle cx="10" cy="12" r="2.2" fill="#c0a870"/><circle cx="10" cy="12" r="1" fill="#e8d090"/></svg>
          <svg width="20" height="26" viewBox="0 0 20 26" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true"><ellipse cx="10" cy="4" rx="5" ry="3.5" fill="none" stroke="#7a6535" stroke-width="2"/><rect x="3" y="6" width="14" height="12" rx="2" fill="#9a8050"/><rect x="1" y="16" width="18" height="6" rx="2" fill="#7a6535"/><circle cx="10" cy="12" r="2.2" fill="#c0a870"/><circle cx="10" cy="12" r="1" fill="#e8d090"/></svg>
        </div>

        <section>
          <h2>1. What is Custom40k?</h2>
          <p>Custom40k is a complete, ready-to-play homebrew ruleset for Warhammer 40,000 that has
            been in development for the past 2+ years and has become the default system for a
            local group of about ~15 people. The rules aim to modernise, streamline, and rebalance
            the "classic era" rules (3rd–7th edition) while still supporting every model GW has ever
            made across all armies, and bringing back army and model customisation via extensive
            armories for every faction.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>2. What are the key differences to current 40k?</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Alternating activation:</strong> Each player only activates one unit at a
              time, which leads to less downtime and less lethality.</li>
            <li><strong>Backwards compatibility:</strong> Every model that GW released for Warhammer
              (and will release in the future) is playable and supported with rules.</li>
            <li><strong>Balance:</strong> Since its inception, Custom40k has been finetuned over
              100+ games to ensure that all units are playable and have a purpose in the game.
              Points are calculated using a unified points calculator. Balancing for a game like 40k
              is an ever ongoing endeavour, but I'm doing my best to keep all armies and units on an
              even level.</li>
            <li><strong>Huge customisation:</strong> Where GW has a strict "No model, no rules"
              policy, "Customisation" is the name of the game. Each faction features their own,
              ever expanding armory full of options for character models, units and army
              composition. Kitbashing and creativity is explicitly desired.</li>
            <li><strong>Old school systems:</strong> Armor Values for vehicles and the Force
              Organisation Chart are back.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>3. What do you need to play Custom40k?</h2>
          <p>Apart from the regular things for a normal game of Warhammer, what you need in addition
            are so called "Command tokens". Command tokens are used at the beginning of every battle
            round to determine what actions a unit may be allowed to do during its activation. While
            we 3d printed our own tokens for this, a suitable replacement would be a simple deck of
            cards for each player. You need four different cards (hearts, diamonds, spades, clover)
            as there are 4 different commands.</p>
        </section>

        <div class="card-cta">
          <a href="/factions" class="cta">Browse the factions &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="discord-card reveal">
      <svg class="discord-card-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M20.317 4.492c-1.53-.69-3.17-1.2-4.885-1.49a.075.075 0 0 0-.079.036c-.21.369-.444.85-.608 1.23a18.566 18.566 0 0 0-5.487 0 12.36 12.36 0 0 0-.617-1.23A.077.077 0 0 0 8.562 3c-1.714.29-3.354.8-4.885 1.491a.07.07 0 0 0-.032.027C.533 9.093-.32 13.555.099 17.961a.08.08 0 0 0 .031.055 20.03 20.03 0 0 0 5.993 2.98.078.078 0 0 0 .084-.026c.462-.62.874-1.275 1.226-1.963.021-.04.001-.088-.041-.104a13.201 13.201 0 0 1-1.872-.878.075.075 0 0 1-.008-.125c.126-.093.252-.19.372-.287a.075.075 0 0 1 .078-.01c3.927 1.764 8.18 1.764 12.061 0a.075.075 0 0 1 .079.009c.12.098.245.195.372.288a.075.075 0 0 1-.006.125c-.598.344-1.22.635-1.873.877a.075.075 0 0 0-.041.105c.36.687.772 1.341 1.225 1.962a.077.077 0 0 0 .084.028 19.963 19.963 0 0 0 6.002-2.981.076.076 0 0 0 .032-.054c.5-5.094-.838-9.52-3.549-13.442a.06.06 0 0 0-.031-.028zM8.02 15.278c-1.182 0-2.157-1.069-2.157-2.38 0-1.312.956-2.38 2.157-2.38 1.21 0 2.176 1.077 2.157 2.38 0 1.312-.956 2.38-2.157 2.38zm7.975 0c-1.183 0-2.157-1.069-2.157-2.38 0-1.312.955-2.38 2.157-2.38 1.21 0 2.176 1.077 2.157 2.38 0 1.312-.946 2.38-2.157 2.38z"/>
      </svg>
      <div class="discord-card-body">
        <div class="discord-card-title">Stay up to date</div>
        <p class="discord-card-text">Questions about the rules, balance updates, or new faction lists? The Custom40k community lives on Discord — come ask, report bugs, or just roll dice with us.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="https://discord.com/invite/wnGAB3TYAY" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="discord-card-btn">
        Join Discord
      </a>
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .intro { max-width: 42rem; margin: 0 auto; text-align: center; }
  .intro-logo { display: block; margin: 0 auto 1rem; object-fit: contain; }
  .intro-title { border-bottom: none; }
  .intro-tagline {
    font-family: var(--font-ui, sans-serif); font-size: 0.72rem; text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em; color: var(--c40k-steel); opacity: 0.7; margin: 0.2rem 0 1.2rem;
    min-height: 1.2em;
  }
  .typing-line {
    border-right: 2px solid var(--c40k-red, #a21217);
    padding-right: 2px;
  }
  .ordo-card-outer { margin: 1.4rem auto 0; max-width: 38rem; width: 100%; }
  .ordo-card section { margin-top: 1.4rem; }
  .ordo-card section:first-of-type { margin-top: 0; }
  .ordo-card section h2 { font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .ordo-card section p, .ordo-card section li { font-size: 0.88rem; line-height: 1.6; text-align: left; }
  .ordo-card ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; }
  .ordo-card li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .card-cta { text-align: center; margin-top: 1.6rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid rgba(162,18,23,0.2); }
  .cta {
    display: inline-block; margin: 1.2rem 0;
    font-family: var(--font-ui, sans-serif); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    font-size: 0.82rem; padding: 0.65rem 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--c40k-red, #a21217); color: var(--c40k-red, #a21217);
    text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; transition: background 0.15s, color 0.15s;
  }
  .cta:hover { background: var(--c40k-red, #a21217); color: #fff; text-decoration: none; }

  /* ── Discord community card ──────────────────────────────── */
  .discord-card {
    max-width: 38rem; width: 100%; margin: 1.6rem auto 0;
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;
    background: rgba(88,101,242,0.07);
    border: 1px solid rgba(88,101,242,0.28);
    border-radius: 6px; padding: 1rem 1.2rem;
  }
  .discord-card-icon {
    width: 36px; height: 36px; flex-shrink: 0;
    fill: #5865F2; opacity: 0.85;
  }
  .discord-card-body { flex: 1; text-align: left; }
  .discord-card-title {
    font-family: var(--font-ui, sans-serif); font-size: 0.72rem;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: #5865F2; margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }
  .discord-card-text {
    font-size: 0.82rem; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--c40k-ink, #2a2420);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .discord-card-btn {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    display: inline-block; padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    font-family: var(--font-ui, sans-serif); font-size: 0.68rem;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: #5865F2; border: 1px solid rgba(88,101,242,0.5);
    border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none;
    background: rgba(88,101,242,0.06);
    transition: background 0.15s, color 0.15s, border-color 0.15s;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .discord-card-btn:hover {
    background: #5865F2; color: #fff; border-color: #5865F2; text-decoration: none;
  }
</style>

<script is:inline>
(function () {
  var el = document.querySelector('.typing-line');
  if (!el) return;
  var text = el.getAttribute('data-text') || '';
  var i = 0;
  function type() {
    el.textContent = text.slice(0, i);
    i++;
    if (i <= text.length) {
      setTimeout(type, 55);
    } else {
      var blinks = 0;
      var iv = setInterval(function () {
        el.style.borderRightColor = blinks % 2 ? '#a21217' : 'transparent';
        blinks++;
        if (blinks > 7) { clearInterval(iv); el.style.borderRight = 'none'; }
      }, 480);
    }
  }
  setTimeout(type, 900);
})();
</script>
